<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="a51a2bf8-69d5-4266-9bd8-e8bb6e95e851" >

    <p>Web accessibility is the practice of removing barriers and creating equal access to information and websites for people with disabilities. It is aimed to address barriers relating to visual, motor, auditory, and cognitive disabilities. Ryerson University is committed to providing an accessible learning and employment environment for students, employees and members of the Ryerson community (Learn more about <a href="/accessibility/" target="_blank">Accessibility at Ryerson)<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a>.</p> 
<p>Brightspace follows web accessibility standards to ensure its interface is made accessible to users with disabilities and assistive technology.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>Ultimately, <strong>it is the responsibility of each course designer or instructor</strong> to ensure course content is formatted using best practices for accessibility; including the use of good heading structure, descriptive link text, alternative text and more.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#a51a2bf8-69d5-4266-9bd8-e8bb6e95e851");});</script></div>

				

				
