<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="4c1fbc7d-3276-4007-bafc-94b000812301" >

    <p>Ensure uploaded content (presentations, PDF’s, YouTube videos, etc.) are built with accessibility in mind.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>All videos should have captions.</li> 
 <li>Avoid using PDF files if possible; formatted HTML is much more accessible. <br> </li> 
 <li>If uploading PDF files, check for accessibility in Acrobat to ensure the document is tagged appropriately.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>Learn more about <a href="/accessibility/tools/accessibledocs/" target="_blank">creating accessible media and documents<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a>.</p>
    





</div>
